	marzi (Recovered): (The grounding exercises actually worked. My chest doesn't feel like it's trapped in a sugar press anymore.)
	marzi (Recovered): Today is the day.
	marzi (Recovered): (She tosses the quilt aside, her movements sharp and purposeful.)
	marzi (Recovered): (I'm going to show Madame Beatrix that I know my way around a copper cauldron.)
	leave marzi
	(She spends a few extra minutes reviewing her flashcards on isomalt humidity tolerances while brushing her teeth.)
