	marzi (Casual Surprised): Oh! Good morning, Madame Sweets!
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): I see you managed to find the establishment without getting distracted.
	beatrix (Macaron): I am glad to see you are taking this opportunity seriously.
	set {beatrix_points} += "10"
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): Punctuality is the foundation of any respectable confectionery.
	marzi (Casual Happy): I wouldn't miss it for the world, Madame!

elif {tired} == "1":
	[background arg="res://backgrounds/BACKGROUND_attic_night.png" fade="0.0"]
	join marzi (Exhausted) left
	marzi (Exhausted): (The alarm blares, but it sounds like it's coming from underwater.)
	marzi (Exhausted): (Marzi groans, her hand blindly smacking the nightstand until it hits the clock.)
	marzi (Exhausted): (Her limbs feel like they've been submerged in dense nougat. Every muscle aches from the tension of a sleepless night.)
	marzi (Exhausted): Ugh... my eyes are burning...
	marzi (Exhausted): I have to get up. I can't be late. I can't afford to be late. Literally.
	leave marzi
	(She drags herself out of bed, fumbling in the dark to find her clothes.)
	(She accidentally puts her shirt on inside out and has to waste precious minutes fixing it, her hands clumsy and shaking.)
	join marzi (Casual Tired) left
	marzi (Casual Tired): (The walk to the bus stop is a miserable blur of cold wind and exhaustion.)
	leave marzi
	[background arg="res://backgrounds/SCENE_bus_ticket_4am.png" fade="3.0" wait="true"]
	[wait time="5.0"]
	[background arg="res://backgrounds/SCENE_bus_tired_4am.png" fade="3.0" wait="true"]
	(On the bus, her head rests against the freezing, vibrating glass of the window.)
	(Her eyelids droop, heavy as lead. She keeps nodding off, only to jerk awake in a sheer panic, terrified she missed the Starlight City stop.)
	(Did I miss it?! No, no, okay, next stop.)
	(She practically falls out of the bus doors when they finally open, breaking into a desperate sprint down the block.)
	(Her lungs burn as the grand, imposing facade of The Gilded Macaron comes into view.)
	[background arg="res://backgrounds/BACKGROUND_gm_outside_4am.png" fade="3.0" wait="true"]
	(She skids to a halt right in front of the heavy doors, gasping for air.)
	join marzi (Casual Sweat) left
	marzi (Casual Sweat): (4\:45 AM. Exactly fifteen minutes early. Not a second to spare.)
	join beatrix (Unimpressed) rightmost
	beatrix (Unimpressed): (A sharp click echoes in the quiet morning air.)
	(Madame Beatrix is standing in the doorway, her thumb resting on the side button of a gleaming golden cell phone.)
	beatrix (Dour Lookdown): Four forty-five. Precisely.
	beatrix (Dour Lookdown): Given your chaotic presentation yesterday, Ms. Glace...
	beatrix (Unimpressed): ...I consider your exact, down-to-the-second arrival a minor miracle.
	marzi (Casual Tired): (Pant... pant...)
	marzi (Casual Tired): I'm here, Madame Sweets. Ready to work.
	beatrix (Dour Lookdown): Try to catch your breath before you contaminate my show room with your panting.
	beatrix (Dour Lookdown): And stand up straight. You look like an unwrapped caramel that has completely lost its shape.
	beatrix (Dour Lookdown): If those dark circles under your eyes are any indication, I expect your focus to be as blurry as your vision today.
	set {beatrix_points} -= "10"
	marzi (Casual Tired): (A weak, desperate smile flickers across her face.)
	marzi (Casual Tired): I-I'm perfectly fine, Madame. Just... eager.
